    <h3><a href="https://stmargarets.london/archives/2018/04/we-know-flooding.html?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=traffic%2Bfrom%20newsletter">We know flooding</a></h3>

    
    <img src="https://stmargarets.london/assets/images/2018/FLOODING_richmond-flood-thumb.jpg" width="150" align="right" style="border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 1px;" alt="" />
    

    <p>The meteorologists said that last month was the wettest March in over a decade - but we knew that already. Living between two rivers, the Thames and the Crane, we St Margarethians have seen the evidence with our own eyes. Twickenham and Richmond riversides were flooded and so were Radnor Gardens, Ranelagh Drive and towpaths from Teddington to Kew and beyond. Cars bobbed about axle deep in murky waters…</p>

