    <p>The historian F.C Hodgson described her as  <em>"one of our undoubted Twickenham celebrities"</em>. Others saw her as an adventurer, an orientalist, a medical pioneer, a correspondent with the good and great and a heart breaker too.</p>

<p>Lady Mary Pierrepont,  the eldest child of Evelyn Pierrepont, 1<sup>st</sup> Duke of Kingston-upon-Hull was born in May 1689. Following his wife's death in 1692 the Duke passed the care of Mary and her three younger siblings to their grandmother.</p>

